"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-what-to-what-paris-olympics-august-2-caeleb-dressel-regan-smith-teddy-riner\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Day 7 of the Olympics is here, and it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s shaping up to be a big one.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 69, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Action continues in the pool and starts on the track, but there are also some fun things to look out for in a few of the lesser-known sports.\", \"from\": 70, \"to\": 211, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My daily guide will help you know what to watch.\", \"from\": 212, \"to\": 260, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You should also subscribe toSports Illustrated\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Daily Rings, the podcast where Dan Gartland and I recap everything every night, with new episodes published before NBC\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s prime-time coverage is even over.\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 348, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"score\": 0.9999998404232556, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gartland\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s what I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll be watching Friday, August 2.\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 521, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not a comprehensive list;visit Olympics.comfor a full schedule.\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 594, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All events will stream live on Peacock.\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 626, \"end\": 633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999991409403317, \"rank\": 4.484006887132028e-07, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll also be tweeting out a schedule of medal events, Team USA games and other favorites each day.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My Day 7 Olympics viewing guide!\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 769, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A monster day.\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 784, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The big stuff is easy to see.But also: I unironically love trampoline, and this is the only day to see it.\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And French judo legend Teddy Riner competes.\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 936, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 896, \"end\": 902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9614697561164395, \"rank\": 0.039738032738204705, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 915, \"end\": 926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And hello, kayak cross!#Paris2024pic.twitter.com/53t8SaE6qG  It should be another raucous night in the pool, with the race known as the splash and dash, the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 50-meter free.\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 1116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 948, \"end\": 953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayaking\", \"score\": 0.5517988683351014, \"rank\": 0.8122545321910646, \"text\": \"kayak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayaking\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayaking\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just one length of the pool, the shortest race at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1194, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"American Caeleb Dressel is the defending Olympic champion, and he has a chance to get back on the podium.\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1195, \"end\": 1203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9942982064834888, \"rank\": 0.005716089455715902, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1204, \"end\": 1218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caeleb Dressel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 200-meter backstroke should also be a great race, with American Regan Smith gunning for a medal after winning silver in the 200m butterfly Thursday.\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1370, \"end\": 1378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9942982064834888, \"rank\": 0.005716089455715902, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1379, \"end\": 1390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2715646650571994e-23, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And L\\u00c3\\u00a9on Marchand will compete in the 200-meter IM, after we already saw him win golds in the 400 IM,200 breaststroke and 200 flyin front of his home crowd.\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1475, \"end\": 1483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999978410779135, \"rank\": 2.156123228875614e-06, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking of French athletes, let\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s talk judo.\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1636, \"end\": 1642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9614697561164395, \"rank\": 0.039738032738204705, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you haven\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t watched any, this is the day to do it.\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Heavyweight Teddy Riner is a legend of the sport.\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1777, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1740, \"end\": 1751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Remember we saw him light the Olympic cauldron during the opening ceremony, which should give you some idea of how good he is.\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is his fifth Olympics.\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 1933, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He already has four individual medals, plus a gold in the team event, which was new in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 2027, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2021, \"end\": 2026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9317410899292321, \"rank\": 0.07325951703381024, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s going for his third individual gold, and the gym will be going crazy.\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2104, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Action starts at 4 a.m.\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2128, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET, and the finals have been starting around 11:30 a.m.\", \"from\": 2129, \"to\": 2184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET (should he make it through).\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Trampoline gymnastics!\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2240, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s only a one-day event, so this is your only chance to see it.\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2308, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The trampolinists bounce eight meters high (about 26 feet), and routines are made up of 10 separate elements\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094all kinds of flips and twists and tucks\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094scored on difficulty and execution.\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2497, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll have qualifications and then finals.\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s finals are at 7:50 a.m.\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET and the men at 1:50 p.m.\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2611, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve never seen it, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s worth checking out.\", \"from\": 2612, \"to\": 2665, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 2667, \"to\": 2693, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Mitch Goldich is a senior editor for Sports Illustrated, mostly focused on the NFL.\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2841, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2758, \"end\": 2763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Mitch\", \"score\": 0.9998247544026837, \"rank\": 0.0001718350197091355, \"text\": \"Mitch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Mitch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Mitch\"}, {\"begin\": 2795, \"end\": 2813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.985099637941466e-26, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}, {\"begin\": 2837, \"end\": 2840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1966_NFL_season\", \"score\": 0.6829366413648192, \"rank\": 0.3514993566854594, \"text\": \"NFL\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1966_NFL_season\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1966_NFL_season\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has also covered the Olympics extensively and written on a variety of sports since joining SI in 2014.\", \"from\": 2842, \"to\": 2947, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His work has been published by The New York Times, Baseball Prospectus and Food & Wine, among other outlets.\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 3056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2979, \"end\": 2997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"score\": 0.9999999999713509, \"rank\": 2.8785704830909707e-11, \"text\": \"The New York Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Goldich has a bachelor\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in journalism from Lehigh University and a master\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in journalism from the Medill School at Northwestern University.\", \"from\": 3057, \"to\": 3202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3103, \"end\": 3109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lehigh_Mountain_Hawks_football\", \"score\": 0.9763730216647489, \"rank\": 0.023569830423967753, \"text\": \"Lehigh\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lehigh_Mountain_Hawks_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lehigh_Mountain_Hawks_football\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is a Philly native, now living in Boston, and he invented and popularized the octopus, when the same player scores a touchdown and the ensuing two-point conversion.\", \"from\": 3203, \"to\": 3370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3240, \"end\": 3246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"score\": 0.9200961894809916, \"rank\": 0.08681517542245211, \"text\": \"Boston\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC.\", \"from\": 3372, \"to\": 3449, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 3450, \"to\": 3472, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only.\", \"from\": 3473, \"to\": 3549, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands.\", \"from\": 3550, \"to\": 3744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3677, \"end\": 3695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.985099637941466e-26, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit.\", \"from\": 3745, \"to\": 3833, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-8